[## LECTURE 6.5 — BACKUP AND RESTORE: MEASURED RTO]

82
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Backups are useless if you cannot restore them.
SOC 2 requires regular restore testing.
Let me show you how to automate quarterly restore drills.

83
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Create a restore test script.
First, get the latest automated RDS snapshot.

84
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
aws rds describe-db-snapshots for the production instance.
Filter by snapshot type automated.
Sort by creation time and take the latest.

85
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Restore a new RDS instance from that snapshot.
Use a test instance name like financial-rag-restore-test.
Use a small instance class to save cost.

86
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Wait for the instance to become available.
aws rds wait db-instance-available.
Measure the time taken. This is your database RTO.

87
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Once the instance is available, get its endpoint.
Connect and verify data integrity.
Count the number of rows in analysis_history.

88
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Now restore the application from Velero.
Get the latest backup name.
velero backup get with JSON output and sort by completion timestamp.

89
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Create an isolated test namespace.
velero restore create with namespace mapping.
Wait for the restore to complete.

90
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Measure the time taken for application restore.
Count the number of API pods running in the test namespace.

91
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Clean up. Delete the test RDS instance.
Delete the test namespace.
Both can be done in parallel.

92
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Calculate total RTO.
Database restore seconds plus application restore seconds.
For SOC 2, your RTO target should be four hours.

93
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Generate a restore test report in markdown.
Include the date, RTO target, database restore duration,
application restore duration, total RTO, and rows verified.

94
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Upload the report to the immutable evidence bucket.
aws s3 cp with SSE KMS.
Schedule this script as a quarterly CronJob.

95
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Your lab exercise is to run a backup restore test.
Verify you can restore from the latest snapshot and query data.
Document the restore duration and any issues encountered.

96
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
In the next lecture, we will build an SLO dashboard.
Prove availability in real time.


