[## LECTURE 6.6 — SLO DASHBOARD: PROVE AVAILABILITY IN REAL TIME]

97
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
You have all the components.
But how do you know if you are meeting your availability SLO?
You need a dashboard that shows real-time availability, error budget,
and historical trends.

98
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Create Prometheus recording rules for availability metrics.
First, rag colon availability colon rate5m.
Sum of rate of successful queries over five minutes
divided by sum of rate of all queries over five minutes.

99
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Second, rag colon availability colon rate30d.
Same calculation over thirty days instead of five minutes.
This is your rolling SLO.

100
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Third, rag colon error budget remaining colon rate30d.
One minus one minus availability divided by one minus zero point nine nine nine.
Zero point nine nine nine is your SLO target of ninety-nine point nine percent.

101
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
If this number goes below zero, you have exceeded your error budget.
Your SLA is failing.

102
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Fourth, rag colon downtime minutes colon month.
One minus availability times thirty days times twenty-four hours times sixty minutes.
This tells you how many minutes of downtime you have experienced this month.

103
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Fifth, rag colon latency p95 colon rate5m.
Histogram quantile of query latency.
If this exceeds your SLA threshold, customers are experiencing slow responses.

104
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Now create alerts based on these metrics.
First alert. SLOBurnRateCritical.
If one minus five-minute availability is greater than five times the error budget rate.
For example, if you are burning through your error budget five times faster than allowed.

105
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Second alert. ErrorBudgetLow.
If error budget remaining is less than twenty percent.
This means you have used more than eighty percent of your monthly error budget.

106
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Third alert. P95LatencyHigh.
If p95 latency is greater than three seconds for five minutes.
This indicates performance degradation even if the API is still technically available.

107
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Apply the PrometheusRule.
kubectl apply dash f.
Now query the metrics to save as daily evidence.

108
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
curl to Prometheus query for rag colon availability colon rate30d.
Multiply by one hundred to get a percentage.
Output a JSON object with metric name, value, SLO target, and compliant boolean.

109
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Save this as availability-30d dot json in your evidence directory.

110
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Your lab exercise is to create the Prometheus recording rules.
Query the metrics and verify they are being recorded.
Set up the alerts and test that they fire when thresholds are exceeded.

111
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
In the next lecture, we will collect incident response evidence.
On-call schedules and post-incident reviews.


